explanation: The solution uses bitwise operations to count the number of set bits in the binary representation of n. It iteratively checks the least significant bit of n using the bitwise AND operator (&) and then right shifts n using the unsigned right shift operator (>>>). This approach is efficient as it only requires a constant amount of space and has a time complexity that is proportional to the number of bits in n.

